text:
This was my first time to sky dive and I am still in awe ! Skydive the Gulf is completely amazing. I have never met another staff where everyone is so friendly,professional,and most of all they make you feel like they truly care about you!!! From first meeting Rachel at the front desk to get checked in to my instructor Charles, to the pilot of the plane, to everyone else we came in contact with, they were so nice and helpful !  This is a young crew and I am still in awe at how awesome they are in operating this company. As far as my jump, I wasn’t nervous at all because I was very comfortable and secure in everything Charles  had told me in preparation. The jump was incredible and I don’t think my feet will ever totally touch the ground again !!! I am ready to go again and when I do it will be more than worth the miles to go back to Skydive the Gulf. You absolutely can’t go wrong with these guys !!! They are the best by leaps and bounds.  To the staff, thank you so much for one of the greatest adventures in my life and being able to check off number 1 on my bucket list !!!
I pray that you will be safe and be blessed in all of your endeavors!

Thank you from the bottom of my heart,
Anette Wade

name: John DelPrete
text: Skydive The Gulf has structured their business model in order to meet its mission goal, which is to provide you, the tandem student with the best safest and personalized experience possible.  Not the average DZ; commonly know as “Tandem Factories”.  The schedule allows enough time so that they may get to know each of you and for you to know and be comfortable with each of the staff members.  They understand that committing to a skydive is a big decision so enough time is planned to make the experience about you, creating an ever lasting memory filled with awesome.  Tandem skydiving is all that they do.  The philosophy is to eliminate distractions, focus, achieve excellence and become the very best.  Locally owned and operated; the team are not only colleagues but friends with the same mind set and goals, to provide you the tandem student with a safe and personalized experience, as opposed to other DZ’s whose goal is to process as many people in the shortest time possible regardless of weather conditions.   Each team member has the authority to halt operations at any time if safety is a concern.  Safety and your experience are foremost not the bottom line.  “To those who jump no explanation is necessary, to those who don’t jump no explanation is possible.”  What are YOU waiting for?????

resp.text:
Hello Ginger, We would like to sincerly apoligize that you had to drive and were not able to jump. In regaurds to the reason, Saftey is our number one priority! We would never want to put you as our customers or our instructors in danger. Planes do have problems just like cars. We are so sorry that an issue came up in time of you reservation. We Flew a diffrent plane in this evening and we will be back in business first thing tomorrow. Like we explained on the phone we would love for you to skydive with us. If you read any of the reveiws of any one who has jumped with us you will see we are a strong team and we love making our customers happy.
We hope you understand and are able to forgive us.
Blue Skies,
the Team at Skydive The Gulf
